{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a5450bc4-90e5-47a8-9af4-951d5e02c144","content":"The directory appears empty, so I'll answer from my knowledge:\n\nTo switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, make these changes in your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's it. With **MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0**, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner. The `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property was opting you back into the legacy runner. Removing it (or explicitly setting `<UseVSTest>false</UseVSTest>`) enables the new platform.\n\n### Things to be aware of:\n\n1. **CLI changes** — Use `dotnet test` as before, but some command-line switches differ. Run `dotnet test --help` to see the new options.\n2. **`.runsettings`** — Most runsettings are still supported, but review for deprecated nodes.\n3. **Test Explorer** — Works in Visual Studio 17.8+ and VS Code with the C# Dev Kit.\n4. **Extensions** — If you use custom VSTest adapters/loggers, look for their Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents (e.g., TRX reporting is now via `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8479fbe1-3c1d-46f5-a66a-c5e1cbbc81ff","outputTokens":320,"requestId":"E3DA:8E236:161BD4D:18BB654:6A052043"},"id":"5e20b3ca-145f-4de4-ad3f-b3738be3a47e","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:07:24.833Z","parentId":"b7c55199-4817-443d-8dd7-1ce50caa645f"}
